summary: Did you hear the news about Jude Law probably being Yon-rogg and not Mar-vell?
question: Did you hear the news about Jude Law probably being Yon-rogg and not Mar-vell?
answer:
This comes from the leak of those demonic-looking funko toys for the Captain Marvel movie, where there’re no statues named “Mar-vell” but one named “Yon-rogg” that is guaranteed to be Jude Law.

Frankly, at this point, I’m not surprised. They’re doing a “meta-twist” a twist that is only a twist because people that know the source material will understand it, but to anyone else, it means little to nothing. Like the Star Trek reboot, when they “reveal” Cumberbatch’s character is actually Khan, which is not a story relevant surprise, it’s there to make people that know who Khan is go “Holy shit!” It’s designed to give fodder to nerd sites like this one to discuss this development and build up interest, which makes me think, jaded cynic that I am, that these leaks are planned out. But that’s just conspiracy nut talk.

I already said I’m not gonna go watch that movie, so this just gives me more reasons to do so. We know the plot revolves around a Carol without memories, and we know that while they aren’t in a relationship, there’s something akin to “sexual tension” between her and Law’s character. That would’ve been fine if the character was Mar-vell, but sexual tension between brain-reset-Carol and fucking Yon-Rogg brings to memory awful shit like the Marcus deal.

There’s a peeking order in any company, and Bendis was over every other writer, so if Bendis wanted Stark undisposed for his stories, well, Stark was undisposed for everyone. Spencer’s decision to have hologram stark to write around the problem, is both lazy, weirdly hilarious, and passive aggressive as fuck.

If you have questions to ask my IPs, please do, if you wanna shitpost, well, I guess if it’s on topic.

I corrected it after seeing this post, thank you very much. Ican’t wait to be done with this, but it’s a long way.
